message: edited this down as it was time to compromise with another editor. 100% within Wiki's guidelines now. cheers!
deleted the section that was not sourced from the article cited

From Wiki:  Self-published expert sources may be considered reliable when produced by an established expert on the subject matter, whose work in the relevant field has previously been published by reliable, independent publications.  I realize there is a difference of opinion here but these are the guidelines set by Wiki. I'm not being told that this article has it's own unique guidelines but I have to go to another article to find them, which seems a bit absurd.
